## Validation Patterns

### Pattern 1: Entity Exists Check

```typescript
const existingEntity = findFlatEntityByIdInFlatEntityMaps({
  flatEntityId,
  flatEntityMaps,
});

if (!isDefined(existingEntity)) {
  validationResult.errors.push({
    code: MyEntityExceptionCode.MY_ENTITY_NOT_FOUND,
    message: t`Entity not found`,
    userFriendlyMessage: msg`Entity not found`,
  });
  return validationResult;
}
```

### Pattern 2: Uniqueness Check

**⚠️ Performance Warning:** `Object.values()` with `.find()` is O(n) and costly for large datasets. Prefer using indexed maps (e.g., `byName`, `byKey`) for uniqueness checks.

#### ❌ Avoid: Iterating with Object.values (O(n))

```typescript
// BAD: Slow for large datasets
const duplicateEntity = Object.values(optimisticFlatMyEntityMaps.byId).find(
  (entity) =>
    entity.name === flatMyEntity.name &&
    entity.id !== flatMyEntity.id
);
```

#### ✅ Prefer: Use indexed maps (O(1))

```typescript
// GOOD: Use an indexed map for O(1) lookup
const existingEntityWithName = optimisticFlatMyEntityMaps.byName[flatMyEntity.name];

if (isDefined(existingEntityWithName) && existingEntityWithName.id !== flatMyEntity.id) {
  validationResult.errors.push({
    code: MyEntityExceptionCode.MY_ENTITY_ALREADY_EXISTS,
    message: t`Entity with name ${flatMyEntity.name} already exists`,
    userFriendlyMessage: msg`An entity with this name already exists`,
  });
}
```

**Note:** If you need to check uniqueness by a property, ensure your flat entity maps include an index for that property (e.g., `byName`, `byKey`). Add it to your `FlatMyEntityMaps` type if needed.

### Pattern 3: Relation Validation

```typescript
const relatedEntity = findFlatEntityByIdInFlatEntityMaps({
  flatEntityId: flatMyEntity.parentEntityId,
  flatEntityMaps: optimisticParentEntityMaps,
});

if (!isDefined(relatedEntity)) {
  validationResult.errors.push({
    code: MyEntityExceptionCode.PARENT_ENTITY_NOT_FOUND,
    message: t`Parent entity not found`,
    userFriendlyMessage: msg`The parent entity does not exist`,
  });
}
```

### Pattern 4: Standard Entity Protection

```typescript
if (!buildOptions.isSystemBuild && belongsToTwentyStandardApp(existingEntity)) {
  validationResult.errors.push({
    code: MyEntityExceptionCode.MY_ENTITY_IS_STANDARD,
    message: t`Cannot modify standard entity`,
    userFriendlyMessage: msg`Standard entities cannot be modified`,
  });
}
```

